hi, jumping on here real quick to let you all know that the last 48 hours have been insane! I cannot express my gratitude for all the love I've received since the AS8 announcement- I know I haven't been able to get back to everyone, but just know- I see the love and I appreciate it so much! this is a new feeling for me, I didn't get to rejoice this way during my original season- it finally feels like I'm getting my flowers. I'm currently on a boat in Miami enjoy my last weekend off before my very busy schedule for the rest of the year, I love you all so much, and want you all to know that..... I'm happy! thank you, from the bottom of my heart. ❤️‍🔥

EP.5 RUVEAL YOURSELF! @rupaulsdragrace 🏁

PRIDE POLAROID PROJECT 2023 x JUNE 2ND // DAY TWO WITH DRAG QUEEN SUPERSTAR @THEKANDYMUSE  
  
For the second day of my Pride Project, I am honored to share these Polaroids I shot of Kandy Muse beside her boudoir.  
  
Drag queens and kings are the superheroes of the LGBTQI+ community. Their power lies in their self assurance and self acceptance.  
 
In this day and age where LGBTQI rights + the drag art form are constantly under attack in the United States, I feel deeply grateful for queens like Kandy who are championing for freedom and fighting against homophobia and transphobia.
  
Their visual representation in society serves as a reminder to all that the LGBTQI+ community is not going anywhere.   
  
If you haven't already, please support the #DragDefenseFund powered by the @aclu_nationwide and catch Kandy on the current All Stars season of @rupaulsdragrace   
  
A few words by Kandy about what pride means to them, "Pride is about celebration, pride is about liberation- and this year, the only difference between this pride and last pride is that we're amplifying x100- they can try to stop us, but in the end, we always win! celebrate your gay pride!"
Kandy Muse on @goodmorningamerica @rupaulsdragrace

october tour dump 👻

entering the last year of my 20's era! 🎈

turning 29 while touring the world is wild, I remember auditioning for drag race when I was 25 like it was yesterday! this year has been nothing but a wild, wild ride! I'm still learning, I'm still making mistakes, and I'm still learning how to love myself even more each day. I'm entering the last year of my 20's as a bad ass bitch, knowing my worth. HERE'S TO 29!!!!! ❤️‍🔥

📸: @andyonderstal

and that's a wrap on werq the world 2023! 👏

wow, I don't think it's even possible to fit all the memories, laughs and adventures into just 10 instagram photos. touring the world the past 2 months has been nothing but fucking amazing! to the fans, thank you for the bottom of my heart for making every single night so magical for me and the girls. to our amazing crew, thank you for all of the hard work you do, lord knows it takes a village to put on this show! 
performing in arenas around the world has truly been nothing but a dream come true. 

now, it's time to go home and go to sleep! ❤️
